quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Creating a Circle[/h1]

A rectangle can be turned into a circle using only CSS. 
To create a circle, the border radius should be half of the height and the width. 

The rectangle in the example below has a width and height of 200px. By setting the border radius to [b]100px[/b], the corners will be rounded to form a circle:[code format="css" codeId="582"]div {
   width: [b]200px[/b];
   height: [b]200px[/b];
   [b]border-radius: 100px;
[/b]   background-color: green;
   color: white;
}[/code]
